1
00:00:08,974 --> 00:00:09,695
Good evening.

2
00:00:09,836 --> 00:00:11,678
I trust you had a fruitful day.

3
00:00:11,919 --> 00:00:14,981
I do not say happy, though I hope it has been happy.

4
00:00:15,964 --> 00:00:31,843
Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sambha Sambhu Tassa Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sambha Sambhu Tassa

5
00:00:32,531 --> 00:00:41,064
Namo tassa bhagavato arahato samma sambuddhasa.

6
00:00:41,085 --> 00:00:45,573
Homage to the Buddha, the blessed, noble and fully self-awakened one.

7
00:00:47,915 --> 00:00:56,850
So I've chosen from our modern point of view, our present day point of view, a rather strange discourse.

8
00:00:57,531 --> 00:01:00,396
It's entitled the Dog Duty Aesthetic.

9
00:01:01,591 --> 00:01:07,864
Aesthetics are well known in most religions.

10
00:01:08,745 --> 00:01:20,950
As you know, the Buddha himself underwent certain aesthetic practices, especially the process of drawing the body down through eating less and less and less, which was more of a Jain practice.

11
00:01:21,722 --> 00:01:29,090
And in the medieval ages, sorry, in the early Christian ages were ascetics who lived on top of pillars.

12
00:01:29,772 --> 00:01:37,078
And they would come down every so often, but they would stay there for quite some time, lowering their chamber pots, I think.

13
00:01:37,819 --> 00:01:46,328
And in the medieval ages, the anchorites, they were men and women who locked themselves into a room in a cathedral and stuff.

14
00:01:46,668 --> 00:01:50,093
Most famous, of course, was Julian of Norwich, who's worth reading.

15
00:01:50,545 --> 00:01:59,903
So there was this very strong element in all religious traditions of a sort of fierce asceticism.

16
00:02:01,206 --> 00:02:07,879
But there's nothing quite like this in the West because this is on the basis of rebirth, of reincarnation.

17
00:02:09,967 --> 00:02:11,530
So here we have the Blessed One.

18
00:02:11,569 --> 00:02:13,171
He's living in a Kolean country.

19
00:02:14,013 --> 00:02:17,598
And two people have come to see him.

20
00:02:17,657 --> 00:02:23,625
Puna, who was one of the Kolean, was an ox duty ascetic.

21
00:02:23,645 --> 00:02:28,270
And also Senea, a naked dog duty ascetic.

22
00:02:28,290 --> 00:02:36,020
And Puna, the ox duty ascetic, paid homage to the Blessed One, sat by one side, and they both exchanged greetings.

23
00:02:36,100 --> 00:02:38,524
And after the Curtis and Amy book talk was finished,

24
00:02:39,162 --> 00:02:41,144
Puna addressed the blessing.

25
00:02:41,883 --> 00:02:48,889
Venerable sir, this Senea is a naked dog duty ascetic who does what is hard to do.

26
00:02:49,570 --> 00:02:52,574
He eats his food when it's his throne on the ground.

27
00:02:53,373 --> 00:02:58,378
He has long taken up a practice of dog duty ascetic, dog duty.

28
00:02:59,118 --> 00:03:02,002
So you can imagine him there sitting like a dog.

29
00:03:03,723 --> 00:03:05,044
What will be his destination?

30
00:03:05,104 --> 00:03:06,725
What will be his future course?

31
00:03:07,486 --> 00:03:09,068
Enough Puna, let that be.

32
00:03:09,335 --> 00:03:10,997
Do not ask me that.

33
00:03:11,758 --> 00:03:20,349
A second time and a third time, the ox duty ascetic asked the Blessed One, Venerable Sir, this Suneer is a naked dog duty ascetic.

34
00:03:20,389 --> 00:03:22,092
What will be his destination?

35
00:03:22,211 --> 00:03:23,754
What will be his future course?

36
00:03:24,656 --> 00:03:29,943
Well, Poonah, since I certainly cannot persuade you when I say, Enough, Poonah, let that be.

37
00:03:30,103 --> 00:03:31,044
Do not ask me.

38
00:03:31,425 --> 00:03:32,646
I shall therefore answer you.

39
00:03:34,209 --> 00:03:38,835
Here, Poonah, someone develops the dog duty fully and uninterruptedly.

40
00:03:39,354 --> 00:03:43,900
He develops the dog duty habit fully and uninterruptedly.

41
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:49,007
He develops the dog duty mind fully and uninterruptedly.

42
00:03:49,167 --> 00:03:54,432
And he develops dog behavior fully and uninterrupted.

43
00:03:55,694 --> 00:04:02,663
Having done so on the dissolution of the body after death, he will reappear in the company of dogs.

44
00:04:03,638 --> 00:04:14,266
And if he has such a view as this, by this virtue or observance or asceticism or holy life, I shall become a great god or lesser god.

45
00:04:14,707 --> 00:04:16,309
That is wrong view in this case.

46
00:04:17,069 --> 00:04:20,892
Now, there are two destinations for one with wrong view, I say.

47
00:04:21,452 --> 00:04:23,634
Hell or the animal realm.

48
00:04:24,196 --> 00:04:29,800
So, Puna, if his dog duty succeeds, it will lead him to the company of dogs.

49
00:04:30,221 --> 00:04:32,682
And if it fails, it will lead him to hell.

50
00:04:33,928 --> 00:04:38,834
Now when this was said, Senea, the naked dog ascetic, cried out and burst into tears.

51
00:04:39,095 --> 00:04:39,574
Well, you would.

52
00:04:41,276 --> 00:04:49,726
Then the Blessed One said to Puna the son, Puna, I could not persuade you when I said enough, Puna, do not ask me this.

53
00:04:49,747 --> 00:04:56,814
Then Senea, the naked dog ascetic, said, Venerable sir, I am not crying because the Blessed One has said this about me.

54
00:04:56,980 --> 00:05:01,245
but because I have long taken up and practiced this dog duty asceticism.

55
00:05:01,666 --> 00:05:06,793
In other words, he's very quickly recognized that it's been a waste of time.

56
00:05:07,355 --> 00:05:11,901
Worse than that, it's been worse than a waste of time.

57
00:05:11,922 --> 00:05:14,706
He's now developed the dog duty mind.

58
00:05:14,725 --> 00:05:16,668
He's developed mind like a dog.

59
00:05:19,833 --> 00:05:22,396
So then, of course, he says, look,

60
00:05:24,367 --> 00:05:27,673
My friend Puna, son of the Kalians, is an ox duty ascetic.

61
00:05:28,334 --> 00:05:30,939
He's long taken up and practiced the ox duty.

62
00:05:31,279 --> 00:05:32,341
What's his destination?

63
00:05:32,362 --> 00:05:34,146
What will his future course be?

64
00:05:34,505 --> 00:05:35,869
Do not ask me that.

65
00:05:37,552 --> 00:05:43,783
First and second time, Venerable Sir, this Puna, son of the Kalians, is an ox duty ascetic.

66
00:05:44,144 --> 00:05:46,127
He's taken up this practice a long time.

67
00:05:46,206 --> 00:05:47,709
What will be his destination?

68
00:05:48,415 --> 00:05:54,403
Senea, since I certainly cannot persuade you when I say enough, Senea, let that be.

69
00:05:54,442 --> 00:05:55,444
Do not ask me that.

70
00:05:55,904 --> 00:05:56,946
I shall therefore answer you.

71
00:05:57,826 --> 00:06:17,392
Senea, someone who develops the ox duty fully and interruptedly, the ox duty habit fully and interruptedly, ox duty mind, and the ox behavior fully and uninterruptedly, having done so on the dissolution of the body after death, he reappears in the company of oxen.

72
00:06:17,845 --> 00:06:42,738
and if he has such a view that this by this observance or asceticism or holy life i shall become a great god or some lesser god this is wrong view now there are two destinations for one with wrong view i say hell and the animal realm so zinnia if this dog if this ox duty succeeds it will lead him to the company of oxen and if it fails it will lead him to hell

73
00:06:43,495 --> 00:06:48,600
When this was said, Pooner, son of the Koreans, the ox dutyer, said he cried out and burst into tears.

74
00:06:48,860 --> 00:06:49,661
Well, he would, wouldn't he?

75
00:06:50,423 --> 00:06:57,932
And then the Blessed One, Sania, said to the dogger, said, Sania, I could not persuade you when I said enough, Sania, let that be, do not ask me.

76
00:06:58,773 --> 00:07:08,845
Venerable sir, says Pooner, I'm not crying because the Blessed One has said this about me, but because I have taken, I have long taken up and practiced the ox duty.

77
00:07:09,432 --> 00:07:14,877
So again, this ox duty ascetic realizes his big mistake.

78
00:07:15,697 --> 00:07:18,360
And he says, I have confidence in the Blessed One thus.

79
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:29,992
The Blessed One is capable of teaching me the Dharma in such a way I can abandon this ox duty and that this sinea, the naked dog ascetic, can abandon his dog duty.

80
00:07:32,053 --> 00:07:34,697
Then he says, well, listen to what I have to say.

81
00:07:35,656 --> 00:07:45,165
There are four kinds of actions proclaimed by me after realizing them for myself with direct knowledge, direct experience.

82
00:07:45,185 --> 00:07:48,088
There is dark action with dark result.

83
00:07:48,870 --> 00:07:51,353
There is bright action with bright result.

84
00:07:52,033 --> 00:07:56,218
There is dark and bright action with dark and bright result.

85
00:07:56,658 --> 00:08:04,666
And there is action that is neither bright, neither dark nor bright, with neither dark nor bright result.

86
00:08:05,271 --> 00:08:29,473
action that leads to the destruction of action right well you've got to get into the language basically uh this dark action is of course immoral behavior unethical behavior so an ethical behavior leads to unethical results and an ethical moral behavior leads to leads to lovely results and of course most people have a mixture of both

87
00:08:29,774 --> 00:08:33,677
both a little bit on the dark side and a little bit on the bright side.

88
00:08:33,998 --> 00:08:41,745
But there's also a level where there's none of that, and that belongs to the one who is fully liberated.

89
00:08:42,566 --> 00:08:48,731
So that sort of action in the Abhidhamma, this later work, was called kriya, functional.

90
00:08:49,212 --> 00:08:56,980
So most people's actions are either kusala or akusala, skillful or unskillful, wholesome or unwholesome.

91
00:08:57,230 --> 00:09:06,706
But when you become liberated, because there's no self-generation, no selfing going on, no attachment going on, the actions are simply pure.

92
00:09:07,025 --> 00:09:09,630
And of course, the defilements are gone too.

93
00:09:09,791 --> 00:09:18,184
So it's always a wholesome action, but there's no consequence for that person in terms of rebirthing, right?

94
00:09:18,205 --> 00:09:19,506
Because there's no identity with it.

95
00:09:20,448 --> 00:09:21,650
It's just pure action.

96
00:09:26,895 --> 00:09:37,506
So then, of course, he says those with dark action will have afflictive bodily formations, afflictive verbal formations and afflictive mental.

97
00:09:37,527 --> 00:09:51,721
So those people who are acting immorally or unethically will have afflictive, painful, et cetera, mental, verbal and bodily actions.

98
00:09:52,562 --> 00:09:57,347
And they will reappear in such a world that is afflicted, that's painful.

99
00:09:58,369 --> 00:10:05,355
And that's because of this constant rebirthing.

100
00:10:06,857 --> 00:10:07,879
So that's what he says.

101
00:10:07,938 --> 00:10:11,221
This, I say, beings are heirs to their actions.

102
00:10:11,581 --> 00:10:14,345
You're an heir to your actions.

103
00:10:14,365 --> 00:10:22,013
So whatever a previous self did yesterday, this self now has to deal with it.

104
00:10:23,748 --> 00:10:29,735
And so he says the same, of course, with those things that are bright and those things that are dark and bright.

105
00:10:30,195 --> 00:10:34,240
There's a mixture there, okay, of afflictive and unafflictive contacts.

106
00:10:35,221 --> 00:10:46,234
And so unafflictive and afflictive feelings, right, mixed with pain and pleasure, as in the case of human beings and some gods and some beings in the lower worlds.

107
00:10:47,355 --> 00:10:53,501
So the ones who are bright action would end up in the heavenly realm where basically you're happy all the time.

108
00:10:53,919 --> 00:11:00,347
And if, of course, you've done some really bad stuff, you end up in the animal or worse, the hell realm.

109
00:11:00,668 --> 00:11:03,331
But the human beings, it's a bit of mixture of both.

110
00:11:03,371 --> 00:11:16,229
And, of course, that's the blessing of this particular existence because with our bright intelligence, this intuitive awareness, we can find our way out of the problem.

111
00:11:16,330 --> 00:11:18,572
This is not open to people in hell.

112
00:11:18,592 --> 00:11:19,614
They're suffering too much.

113
00:11:20,215 --> 00:11:23,538
Animals, of course, don't have the intelligence and people in the heavens don't.

114
00:11:23,772 --> 00:11:49,527
enjoying life too much and of course remember that these these realms of are mirrored in the human uh in the human life aren't they there are people who uh who are basically so uh caught up in their desires uh that uh so so enjoying themselves because they've got you know billions of pounds or whatever and then they're going to think about the spiritual life

115
00:11:49,506 --> 00:11:56,897
And there are people who are caught up in a sort of an animal existence of drugs, et cetera, et cetera, where the intelligence is dulled.

116
00:11:57,297 --> 00:12:09,514
And there are people, of course, who are in great suffering, either mental suffering or physical suffering, where it's difficult to practice spiritually.

117
00:12:09,813 --> 00:12:10,815
They're sort of lost in it.

118
00:12:11,836 --> 00:12:16,543
So all these realms are just mirrors, really, of what we see in the human realm.

119
00:12:19,256 --> 00:12:34,160
and then finally of course this um uh the neither neither dark nor bright actions that's the one where it's there's there's no consequence um

120
00:12:34,985 --> 00:12:46,686
The volition in abandoning the kind of action that is bright brings bright results and the volition of abandoning the kind which is dark and also with dark and bright results.

121
00:12:46,706 --> 00:12:51,774
So the Arahant, the one who's liberated, is lifted above that sort of duality.

122
00:12:52,657 --> 00:12:57,785
These four kinds of actions I've realized for myself, the Buddha says.

123
00:12:58,322 --> 00:13:02,509
So now Puna, of course, he's the ox, isn't he?

124
00:13:02,690 --> 00:13:03,530
I think he's the ox.

125
00:13:03,551 --> 00:13:04,873
Yes, he's the ox ascetic.

126
00:13:05,855 --> 00:13:07,618
So he's really taken for this.

127
00:13:07,677 --> 00:13:10,422
He's really said, magnificent, Venerable Sir, magnificent.

128
00:13:11,123 --> 00:13:13,886
And he becomes a lay follower from that time onwards.

129
00:13:14,788 --> 00:13:17,513
And the dog duty second also says the same thing.

130
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:31,926
The usual, this lovely phrasing that comes up, turning upright what has been overthrown, revealing what was hidden, showing the way to one who was lost, holding up a lamp in the dark for those with eyesight to see form.

131
00:13:32,407 --> 00:13:35,091
And he also goes to the blessed one.

132
00:13:35,913 --> 00:13:40,902
And he actually wants to receive, he wants to become a bhikkhu.

133
00:13:42,282 --> 00:13:50,721
And when somebody becomes a bhikkhu who's been involved in some other tradition, they have to be on probation for four months.

134
00:13:51,023 --> 00:13:53,187
That's now a rule in the order, you see.

135
00:13:53,749 --> 00:13:57,538
So he put him on probation for four months and then ordained him.

136
00:13:58,961 --> 00:14:00,325
The Buddha, in fact, ordained him.

137
00:14:02,953 --> 00:14:10,985
And so then just the last little paragraph tells us what happens to Saniya, the naked dog duty ascetic.

138
00:14:11,466 --> 00:14:30,936
So he received the ordination from the Blessed One, full admission, and then not long after his full admission, dwelling alone, withdrawn, diligent, ardent and resolute, the Venerable Saniya, by realizing for himself with direct knowledge,

139
00:14:31,220 --> 00:14:44,818
here and now entered upon and abided in that supreme goal of the holy life for the sake of which clansmen rightly go forth from home life into homelessness.

140
00:14:45,679 --> 00:14:53,350
And then this lovely phrase that, these are phrases that you'll find often repeated throughout the discourses.

141
00:14:53,370 --> 00:14:55,894
He directly knew birth is destroyed.

142
00:14:56,312 --> 00:14:58,115
The holy life has been lived.

143
00:14:58,634 --> 00:15:01,177
What had to be done has been done.

144
00:15:01,798 --> 00:15:04,639
There is no more coming to any state of being.

145
00:15:05,441 --> 00:15:09,784
And the Venerable Senia became one of the Arahats.

146
00:15:10,524 --> 00:15:21,534
So although we started off in a sort of gloomy place with somebody behaving like an ox and another one behaving like a dog, it seems as though they finally ended up in a very good place.

147
00:15:22,056 --> 00:15:24,817
And Senia became an Arahat, fully liberated.

148
00:15:25,759 --> 00:15:29,125
So we don't have to choose that particular path.

149
00:15:29,145 --> 00:15:33,533
We don't have to do the dog of duty part to become fully liberated.

150
00:15:34,315 --> 00:15:38,461
We've got a slightly easier part, you might say, of just being ordinary people.

151
00:15:39,864 --> 00:15:40,666
So there we are.

152
00:15:41,567 --> 00:15:47,817
I hope that this discourse on the dog duty aesthetic has been helpful.

153
00:15:48,101 --> 00:16:12,894
of interest and i can only hope that like sania you will be ardent etc with your practice and i trust you'll be fully liberated from all suffering sooner rather than later so we can do a little practice

154
00:16:26,559 --> 00:16:50,543
Pūrāṃ pūjēni Dhammāṃ pūjēni Sāṅgāṃ pūjēni

155
00:16:56,327 --> 00:17:22,638
Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arhato Sambha Sambhudassa Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arhato Sambha Sambhudassa Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arhato Sambha Sambhudassa

156
00:17:23,377 --> 00:17:51,157
Bodham Saranam Gacchami Dhammam Saranam Gacchami Sangam Saranam Gacchami Duthiyampi Bodham Saranam Gacchami Duthiyampi Dhammam Saranam Gacchami

157
00:17:51,863 --> 00:18:18,833
Duthiyampi Sangam Saranam Gacchami Tathiyampi Bodham Saranam Gacchami Tathiyampi Dambam Saranam Gacchami Tathiyampi Sangam Saranam Gacchami

158
00:18:19,656 --> 00:18:46,778
Anathipatha Vairamani Sikapadam Samadhi Ami Adhinadana Vairamani Sikapadam Samadhi Ami Kameshumicacara Vairamani Sikapadam

159
00:18:47,010 --> 00:19:08,107
Samadhi Ami Musavadha Vairamani Sikapadam Samadhi Ami Suramriya Majjhapamadhatana Vairamani Sikapadam

160
00:19:08,375 --> 00:19:16,146
Very good.

161
00:19:25,261 --> 00:19:31,951
So make sure your posture is the expression of the awakened one.

162
00:19:42,107 --> 00:19:50,800
So again, as usual, lifting up from the lower spine and the lower back and the abdomen.

163
00:19:53,465 --> 00:19:54,307
Sitting tall.

164
00:19:54,346 --> 00:20:00,256
Spending a moment relaxing the brow.

165
00:20:00,296 --> 00:20:08,689
The jaw lifts together, teeth apart.

166
00:20:12,887 --> 00:20:13,788
The shoulders.

167
00:20:22,663 --> 00:20:25,086
And hands on the lap, whatever's comfortable.

168
00:20:30,236 --> 00:20:32,018
Just acknowledging that posture.

169
00:20:32,078 --> 00:20:39,891
Energized spine, everything else relaxed.

170
00:20:46,334 --> 00:21:13,792
This body is subject to disease This body is of a nature to fall ill This body has not gone beyond sickness This body is subject to aging

171
00:21:18,346 --> 00:21:20,769
This body has not gone beyond aging.

172
00:21:27,039 --> 00:21:29,844
This body is now in a process of aging.

173
00:21:39,339 --> 00:21:41,383
This body is subject to death.

174
00:21:46,020 --> 00:21:48,743
This body has not gone beyond death.

175
00:21:53,229 --> 00:21:55,111
This body will die.

176
00:21:55,171 --> 00:22:09,867
There is the unborn, undying, uncreated, uncompounded.

177
00:22:16,767 --> 00:22:18,048
The unconditioned.

178
00:22:22,953 --> 00:22:25,837
True refuge, harbour and home.

179
00:22:31,203 --> 00:22:41,256
Perfect peace and contentment.

180
00:22:41,276 --> 00:22:45,441
Those who are mindful are in the presence of Nirvana.

181
00:22:55,546 --> 00:23:14,227
waiting for that settlement upon the breath, then opening up to whatever draws our attention within the field of awareness, just observing, just feeling, just experiencing intimately.

182
00:23:14,247 --> 00:23:17,570
It's enough.

183
01:05:02,780 --> 01:05:31,960
A moment's reflection Resolution

184
01:05:49,000 --> 01:05:52,123
So we can begin our evening contemplations.

185
01:05:52,184 --> 01:05:54,126
Make sure that you're sitting comfortably.

186
01:06:07,242 --> 01:06:09,985
Speaking gently into our own hearts.

187
01:06:13,068 --> 01:06:15,851
May I be free of physical pain.

188
01:06:21,534 --> 01:06:24,684
May I be free of mental distress.

189
01:06:31,362 --> 01:06:34,532
May I be liberated of all my sufferings.

190
01:07:08,887 --> 01:07:11,911
Bringing to mind someone we know is having a hard time.

191
01:07:20,105 --> 01:07:22,648
May you be free of physical pain.

192
01:07:28,018 --> 01:07:31,063
May you be free of mental distress.

193
01:07:37,675 --> 01:07:40,547
May you be liberated of all your sufferings.

194
01:08:13,905 --> 01:08:18,693
And there are all those at this moment who are sick and or suffering from mental illness.

195
01:08:20,595 --> 01:08:26,765
People in the process of dying and those who have died and left grieving family, relatives and friends.

196
01:08:28,787 --> 01:08:32,194
People going hungry, homeless and destitute.

197
01:08:34,737 --> 01:08:39,744
Those having to deal with severe personal and interpersonal difficulties.

198
01:08:42,592 --> 01:08:50,681
All those caught up in wars and repressive regimes and those being tortured.

199
01:08:50,702 --> 01:08:54,546
And there are those suffering from natural disasters and climate crisis.

200
01:08:57,430 --> 01:09:02,355
All the sentient beings are being cruelly treated and unnecessarily slaughtered.

201
01:09:04,457 --> 01:09:09,323
And all who find life meaningless.

202
01:09:09,344 --> 01:09:11,806
May you be free of physical pain

203
01:09:16,815 --> 01:09:19,363
May you be free of mental distress.

204
01:09:24,822 --> 01:09:27,872
May you be liberated of all your sufferings.

205
01:09:56,488 --> 01:10:00,753
Radiating our compassion to all beings in all directions.

206
01:10:01,895 --> 01:10:04,719
May all beings be free of physical pain.

207
01:10:09,664 --> 01:10:12,568
May all beings be free of mental distress.

208
01:10:18,695 --> 01:10:22,260
May all beings be liberated of all their sufferings.

209
01:10:53,137 --> 01:10:57,545
Bringing to mind now some moments of joyfulness we've experienced today.

210
01:10:58,948 --> 01:11:02,073
Happiness, peacefulness.

211
01:11:11,007 --> 01:11:12,411
May I be joyful.

212
01:11:15,536 --> 01:11:17,880
May my joyfulness increase.

213
01:11:22,011 --> 01:11:25,372
May I experience the bliss of liberation.

214
01:11:57,027 --> 01:12:00,489
Bringing to mind someone we know is caused to be joyful.

215
01:12:08,997 --> 01:12:10,300
May you be joyful.

216
01:12:14,543 --> 01:12:16,666
May your joyfulness increase.

217
01:12:23,192 --> 01:12:26,274
May you experience the bliss of awakening.

218
01:12:56,680 --> 01:13:20,146
And to all those at this moment who are happy and content with their lives, who are enjoying the warmth of friendships, enjoying the delights of art and nature, hobbies and so on, who find their work meaningful, who enjoy the fruitfulness of their spiritual lives and who rejoice in the success of others.

219
01:13:21,608 --> 01:13:23,109
May you be joyful.

220
01:13:27,359 --> 01:13:29,609
May your joyfulness increase.

221
01:13:34,408 --> 01:13:37,722
May you experience the bliss of Nirvana.

222
01:14:04,854 --> 01:14:10,983
Radiating our goodwill joy to all beings in all directions.

223
01:14:13,105 --> 01:14:14,747
May you be joyful.

224
01:14:15,229 --> 01:14:17,471
May all beings be joyful.

225
01:14:21,356 --> 01:14:23,460
May your joyfulness increase.

226
01:14:28,527 --> 01:14:32,112
May you experience the bliss of Nirvana.

227
01:15:00,104 --> 01:15:02,426
Allowing these words to flow through us.

228
01:15:03,628 --> 01:15:08,256
If you're wise and want to reach the state of peace, you should behave like this.

229
01:15:09,158 --> 01:15:13,463
You should be upright, responsible, gentle and humble.

230
01:15:14,746 --> 01:15:18,891
Easily contented and need only a few things.

231
01:15:19,872 --> 01:15:24,000
Not always be busy and have the right sort of work.

232
01:15:25,561 --> 01:15:28,947
Your senses should be guarded and you should be modest.

233
01:15:30,596 --> 01:15:33,979
You should not be exclusively attached to only a few people.

234
01:15:35,220 --> 01:15:39,484
And you should not do the slightest thing that a wise person could blame you for.

235
01:15:40,926 --> 01:15:56,801
You should always be thinking, may all beings be happy, whatever living beings there are, be they weak or strong, big or small, large or slender, living nearby or far away, those who have already been born and those who have yet to be born.

236
01:15:57,921 --> 01:15:59,203
May all beings

237
01:15:59,436 --> 01:16:02,819
Without exception, be happy.

238
01:16:02,840 --> 01:16:08,725
You should not tell lies to each other and do not think anyone, anywhere, is of no value.

239
01:16:08,784 --> 01:16:18,172
Do not wish harm to anyone, even when you're angry, just as a mother would protect her only child at the risk of her own life.

240
01:16:18,632 --> 01:16:23,518
So you should let the warmth of your heart go out to all beings.

241
01:16:23,537 --> 01:16:28,801
Let your thoughts of love go through the whole world, above and below, without any barrier.

242
01:16:29,439 --> 01:16:41,498
with no ill will or hatred, whether you're standing, walking, sitting, or lying down, as long as you're awake, you should develop this affectionate mindfulness.

243
01:16:42,600 --> 01:16:44,963
This they say is the noblest way to live.

244
01:16:45,425 --> 01:16:54,840
And if you do not fall into unskillful ways and live well and develop insight and are no longer attached to all the desires of the senses,

245
01:16:55,478 --> 01:16:59,503
then truly you never need to be reborn into this world again.

246
01:17:01,206 --> 01:17:05,552
Please join me in the chanting, or if you wish, offer these blessings.

247
01:17:05,672 --> 01:17:08,277
May you be safe, well and happy.

248
01:17:08,917 --> 01:17:12,283
May you live contented, in harmony with the world.

249
01:17:14,947 --> 01:17:24,000
Karaniyam Ghatakusalena Yandam Santam Padangabhisameca

250
01:17:24,520 --> 01:17:33,314
Sākhojūcā, Suhujūcā, Sūvācchocā, Sāmunūvānāttimāli.

251
01:17:33,333 --> 01:17:42,528
Sāntu Sākhojā, Subhārojā, Apākijocā, Sālāukāuti.

252
01:17:43,488 --> 01:17:51,641
Sāntindayocā, Nīpākojā, Apāgabhokuleśu, Anānukidau.

253
01:17:52,194 --> 01:18:01,047
Nācā kūdhāṃ sā mācāre kañcī, ye nā viṇyu pāre upāvā deyum.

254
01:18:01,068 --> 01:18:09,078
Sukhi no vākemi no hontu, sābe sātā bāvantu sukhi tātām.

255
01:18:10,041 --> 01:18:18,472
Ye keci pāna bhūtati, tāsa vāta vāra vā anā vāse sām.

256
01:18:19,313 --> 01:18:48,324
Dīgāvā ye mahāntavā Majjhī marāsakāru kathulā Dītāvā ye vādhītā Ye cādhūre vāsānti āvidhūre Bhūtāvā sambhāveṣīvā Sābeṣātā bhāvantu sukhi tathā Nāparo parāṅgī kubhata

257
01:18:48,457 --> 01:19:17,417
Nathimanyatakathachinenkenchi Vyarosanapatigasanyananyamanyasadukangiceya Matayataniyangputangayusaikaputanganurake Hevampisabhutesumanasambhavayeapadimana

258
01:19:18,476 --> 01:19:27,029
Metencha sabbalukasmin manasambhavaye aparimanam.

259
01:19:27,050 --> 01:19:35,944
Udangado chatiriancha asampatanga verangasapatam.

260
01:19:35,963 --> 01:19:44,417
Titancharanisino vasayanavayavatasa vigatamido.

261
01:19:45,005 --> 01:20:11,974
Hei tan sa ting adhite ya brahmange tangviharangitamapu Ditin ca anupagama sila vadasanena sampano Kameshuvene agetam nahijatuga bhaseyan punaretiti

262
01:20:14,181 --> 01:20:15,783
May all beings be happy.

263
01:20:16,945 --> 01:20:42,585
Very good.

264
01:20:43,055 --> 01:20:54,011
So I hope you were somewhat amused by the dog aesthetic practice and also the presumed sense of humor of the Buddha.

265
01:20:54,192 --> 01:20:58,118
He comes across as sometimes with wry humor.

266
01:20:58,677 --> 01:21:02,323
He likes to have a little dig at people sometimes too.

267
01:21:03,204 --> 01:21:08,353
So don't forget from now till we fall asleep, he's also about practice.

268
01:21:08,755 --> 01:21:19,574
putting something beautiful into the heart drifting away into sweet oblivion rising in the morning to take to make the best of the day may you sleep peacefully

